    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Let me be more clear: I think contracts should be able to reject payments if they cannot handle them or are unwilling to handle them. Every contract that sends value should be able to handle that condition gracefully.\r\n\r\nAlso, contracts should be allowed to at least log an event when they receive value, as a courtesy payed by the originator of the transaction (as the current semantics of send allow).",
